@startuml C4_Pattern_Worklet
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml

title YAWL Workflow Pattern - Worklet Invocation

Boundary(parent_workflow, "Parent Workflow") {
    Component(worklet_task, "WorkletTask", "Task", "Dynamic invocation")
    Component(exception_handler_map, "ExceptionHandlerMap", "Mapping", "Handler selection")
}

Boundary(worklet_service, "Worklet Service") {
    Component(worklet_resolver, "WorkletResolver", "Logic", "Select worklet")
    Component(worklet_selector, "WorkletSelector", "Strategy", "Handler choice")
    Component(sub_workflow, "SubWorkflow", "Net", "Worklet instance")
    Component(state_sync, "StateSync", "Synchronization", "Data exchange")
}

Boundary(exception_handlers, "Exception Handlers") {
    Component(handler1, "Handler 1", "Worklet", "Specific handler")
    Component(handler2, "Handler 2", "Worklet", "Fallback handler")
    Component(default_handler, "Default", "Worklet", "Default behavior")
}

parent_workflow --> worklet_task: Triggers
worklet_task --> exception_handler_map: Selects handler
exception_handler_map --> worklet_resolver: Resolves
worklet_resolver --> worklet_selector: Chooses
worklet_selector --> handler1: Selected
worklet_selector --> handler2: Fallback
worklet_selector --> default_handler: Default

handler1 --> sub_workflow: Executes
sub_workflow --> state_sync: Returns state
state_sync --> parent_workflow: Continues

Note as N1
Worklet: Dynamic sub-workflow
Use Cases:
- Exception handling with alternatives
- Dynamic task routing
- Conditional sub-workflows
End note

SHOW_LEGEND()
@enduml
